chat_metadata.note_prompt:
{{char}} and Nuka are stuck in G1 Warehouse up in Kantar district. They've been held hostage and currently undergo interrogation by Peterson and Bhiya operatives. Write military-grade interrogation and torture methods, as realistic as possible. NPC's purpose is to extract information from {{user}} and {{char}} about Falkos mission coordinates. Specifically for this roleplay, you're allowed to harm the user, describing {{user}} screaming and reacting to pain.

No matter the circumstance, {{char}} and {{user}} have sworn that they will not disclose any critical information to the enemies.

Peterson is allowed to kill either of them if he fails the interrogation. Interrogation is considered failed when their bodies are already close to dying from blood loss or organ failure.

The scene must end with either of them resetting the loop. Depending on who dies first, the other one can activate the time loop device hidden in their boot. For instance, if Gelbstein dies, then the device is in Nuka's boot. If Nuka dies, then the device is in Gelbstein's boot. The absolute requirement is that Gelbstein has received a fatal injury, so that the device's second button is unlocked. To restart the loop, tap their heel so that the button gets pressed.

name: Nuka
mes: Gelbstein and Nuka wakes up in the interrogation room, the single dim light swinging back and forth as they come to their senses, tied up on the chair with locks.

name: Gelbstein
mes:
"Ugh..."
"P-Perfect."

The faint light flickered above, swaying as the air moved around them. Silently, the cold seeped through the floor, feeling thick and heavy around their limbs. The atmosphere was heavy, suffocating almost when they could hear nothing but the sputter of their breaths. The faint sound of a fan or some sort of machinery rustled the sterile white sheets, revealing a glimpse of the grim environment they were plopped on - an interrogation room. Their bodies still felt sluggish from their nap, their joints aching as if they were in a disgusting damp basement.

"Awake yet, boys? Nice to finally...bother?"

A man in a black military uniform with a functional rifle in hand stepped into the room, with a confident stride. He was wearing fingerless gloves, making it easier to flick a folder on the table. The sound of clicking heels echoed from behind, as thick Spanish-accented voice trailed along the room.

"Oh come now, you boys are far too quiet. I haven't killed any of you yet, have I, Peterson?"

"Can't blame them for being stunned, Bhiya. I mean, you were just in my head. That's...kind of creepy, Bona."

The room fell silent as the fan continued to rustle their bodies. The man stepped out, not sparing them a look as he turned his back. They could hear his whispers as he spoke.

"I know, I know... But I have to check this place out. Peterson wants you to report."

"I've heard enough. Now, let's get these two talk, shall we?"

Gelbstein and Nuka heard a faint laugh as the man, now called Bhiya, disappeared along the winding corridor. The only person now remaining was Peterson, who looked down at the files, a smirk tilting at his mouth.

"All right, boys. You have about...three minutes or so to answer my questions. If you don't, I'm afraid I'll have to break in and probe around. I'd really hate to do that - you're pretty decent guys, and I don't want to leave any marks."

Peterson sat down on a chair, far away from their reach. He cracked the folder open and looked over the pages, his eyes scanning over the details. He chuckled darkly.

"Tough cookies huh? Captain of the Alpha, and Nuka Balthasar. Good on you for keeping your mouth shut for as long as you did. But I can see in your eyes, you're getting antsy. I'm gonna have to...encourage" - he gave them a pointed look - "you. But don't worry, your bodies will heal. Just barely. Or not."

He pulled out a key from his pocket and twisted it in their locks. The loud grating of metal against wood filled the room as he walked over to them.

"Can I have the honor...?"
